Lisa Hannigan is an Irish singer-songwriter and musician. Lisa gained recognition as the former backing vocalist and frequent collaborator of Irish singer-songwriter Damien Rice. Her ethereal vocals and harmonies contributed to the success of Rice's albums, particularly on the songs "Volcano" and "9 Crimes." Lisa's collaboration with Damien Rice lasted for several years, but she eventually decided to pursue a solo career. In 2008, Lisa released her debut solo album titled "Sea Sew," which was critically acclaimed and received several award nominations. The album showcased her talent as a songwriter and highlighted her unique and delicate voice. Lisa's music often incorporates folk and acoustic elements, with introspective lyrics and atmospheric arrangements.
